# API Rule — Contract and Service Standards

All backend services must follow API-first conventions.

## API design
- Use consistent resource naming
- Use versioned APIs
- Prefer explicit DTOs
- Use schema validation for request/response bodies
- Return typed error objects

## Core resources
- organizations
- memberships
- projects
- agents
- apps
- environments
- deployments
- routes
- secrets
- runtime-profiles
- model-configs
- tool-configs

## Error handling
Use structured error responses:
- code
- message
- details (optional)
- requestId

## Validation
All inbound payloads must be validated with a schema library.
Never trust raw request input.

## API boundaries
- controllers handle request/response mapping
- services handle business logic
- repositories handle persistence
- infrastructure clients wrap external systems

## Forbidden patterns
- direct SQL in controllers
- domain logic inside route handlers
- implicit any in API types
- untyped external service responses
